 FILES
A file is a collection of data stored on a computer. It can contain text, images, programs, audio, videos, or other information.
  
  Directories (Folders)
A directory is a container used to organize files and other directories. It helps users arrange data in a hierarchical structure.
  
  File Compression
File compression is a technique used to reduce the size of a file so that it requires less storage space and can be transferred more quickly.

